com.googlecode.cqengine.resultset.order

Class MaterializingResultSet<O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.resultset.ResultSet<O>
      • com.googlecode.cqengine.resultset.order.MaterializingResultSet<O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<O>

    public class MaterializingResultSet<O>
extends ResultSet<O>
    Wraps another ResultSet and ensures that the Iterator returned by the iterator() method never returns the same object more than once.

    This ResultSet does not materialize all objects up-front, rather it starts returning objects from the wrapped ResultSet immediately, and records during iteration the objects issued so far in a temporary collection. If the wrapped ResultSet returns the same object more than once, this ResultSet will transparently skip it and move to the next object.

    Note that the size() method in this implementation has O(n) time complexity, because it uses the deduplicating iterator to count objects.

    Author:
    Niall Gallagher

      • size

        public int size()
        Returns the number of objects which would be returned by this ResultSet if iterated.

        Note that the cost of calling this method depends on the query for which it was constructed.

        For simple queries where a single query is supplied and a matching index exists, or where several such simple queries are supplied and are connected using a simple Or query, calculating the size via this method will be cheaper than iterating through the ResultSet and counting the number of objects individually.

        For more complex queries, where intersections must be performed or where no suitable indexes exist, calling this method can be non-trivial, but it will always be at least as cheap as iterating through the ResultSet and counting the number of objects individually.

        This implementation has O(merge_cost) time complexity, because it delegates to the iterator() method and counts objects returned.

        Specified by:
        size in class ResultSet<O>

        The number of objects which would be returned by this ResultSet if iterated
